A vintage-style illustration of a winding river flowing through a landscape, where the water is composed of glowing blue data fragments and JSON-like curly brackets, breaking apart into individual droplets as it passes through an old wooden water mill. The mill's wheel catches each droplet separately, transforming the continuous flow into discrete parcels. Warm sepia tones dominate the scene with pops of electric blue from the data stream. Autumn trees line the riverbanks, their leaves resembling small document icons gently falling. The sky has the aged, slightly yellowed quality of an old photograph, with soft clouds. The perspective follows the river from a hillside vantage point, emphasizing the journey of continuous flow becoming individual pieces.
